cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE

The paper presents a new implementation of t-SNE, a commonly used technique for visualizing high-dimensional data in scatter plots. The implementation uses vantage-point trees and a variant of the Barnes-Hut algorithm, which are both commonly used in machine learning and computational science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of sparse pairwise similarities and the approximation of forces between points, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
